text: Jennifer Flynn Oldenburg (born 26 July 1978) is an American volleyball player and coach. She was a member of the United States women's national volleyball team. She played at the 2002 FIVB World Championship. She graduated from Ohio State University. She coached for University of Illinois and Ohio State University. == References == == Other websites == * USA - Player's biography Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:American volleyball players Category:American volleyball coaches
